		<h1><a href="http://foodsense.is/blog/the-spork-sisters">The Sisters Who Inspire Everyone to Cook Vegan</a></h1>
		<h2>My Veg Life</h2>	</header>
		
	<div class="group">
		<img src="http://foodsense.is/uploads/post-images/SporkMacCheese_blog.jpg" class="post-image border" alt="image" />		<p><em>If you&#8217;ve ever taken a cooking class with these sisters, you know that Jenny Engel and Heather Goldberg are incredibly inspiring, knowledgeable, and fun. Together, Jenny and Heather run <a href="http://sporkfoods.com">Spork Foods</a>, a Los Angeles-based gourmet vegan food company offering live cooking classes in Los Angeles, <a href="http://sporkonline.com">online vegan cooking classes</a>, one-on-one in-home healthy pantry makeovers, and recipe development/trainings for chefs, food companies and colleges. Their cookbook, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Spork-Fed-Super-Flavorful-Recipes-Sisters/dp/0983272611/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1317210395&amp;sr=8-1">Spork-Fed</a>, will be released in three short days, on October 1, with a foreword by fellow fans and sisters, Emily and Zooey...</em></p>
		<p><a href="http://foodsense.is/blog/the-spork-sisters">Continue reading &raquo;</a></p>	</div>
	
